<subSubSection id="D47A377F85461A668B5157353ABBD620" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E6B11A11BF239C35898EC689FCC0A811" lastPageNumber="62" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicName id="2DD2E529F77BD3BEF62EF160E1FF4128" pageNumber="61" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Glyptosternina">Glyptosternina</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from other clades of sisorids by the combination of no adhesive apparatus on the thorax and the presence of plaited adhesive organs on the paired fins (Fig. 15). Osteological traits used by de Pinna (1996) to diagnose 
<taxonomicName id="2486B4FB5415A9622FE409132959C5CD" pageNumber="61" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Glyptosternina">Glyptosternina</taxonomicName>
include maxilla dorsoventrally flat and strongly expanded distally; interopercle narrow and elongate, its laminar portion reduced; proximal pectoral radials 2 and 3 flared at distal 
<pageStartToken id="EF1A9B47AD782F264F6382926184BECD" pageNumber="62">tip</pageStartToken>
; and external arm of basipterygium abruptly expanded distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D8B7E314D41DF6E113A89C8CBC6F35FF" pageNumber="62">
He (1996b), using mostly osteological characters, found 
<taxonomicName id="BEF10379C64783A8A51AF10C43C892BA" pageNumber="62" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Glyptosternina">Glyptosternina</taxonomicName>
to be a monophyletic group defined by the following 12 apomorphies: 1) Posterior tip of lateral ethmoid prolonged and extended to the margin of the cranium. 2) Anterior part of frontal very narrow, its width far smaller than that of the posterior part. 3) Tooth band in upper jaw narrow, without posterolateral extensions (plesiomorphic in 
<taxonomicName id="CCC50A6047782F7AB09CFBAB7FACAF04" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F34DE64E-5530-4CC0-A5C5-3BD58430405D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Glyptosternon" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Glyptosternon McClelland 1842:584" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Glyptosternon</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="25F088558A961E3B9B75BD366074DE86" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:27BFA05B-0A54-4C56-AE35-8F7CCEEC4577" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Euchiloglanis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Euchiloglanis Regan 1907:158" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Euchiloglanis</taxonomicName>
). 4) Articular very short and small, wedge-like, attaching to the posterior end of the dentary (plesiomorphic in 
<taxonomicName id="63B54653DFA616E8D128E5E67CA9E04C" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:987310A1-9E85-4272-AD9D-9DB5D24D6779" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Exostoma" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Exostoma Blyth 1860:155" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Exostoma</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="04024E9796395C156C2B2F12F41EF43F" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25654FA9-3B1D-4464-8012-AEE3D499BCEB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Glaridoglanis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Glaridoglanis Norman 1925:574" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Glaridoglanis</taxonomicName>
). 5) Autopalatine enormously developed, broad, strong and spatulate at both ends. 6) Interoperculum long and thin, as long as the length from the anterior tip of the dentary to its posterior end). 7) Dorsal neural spine of the 4th vertebra undeveloped, plate-like, single, not connected to the proximal radial of the dorsal fin; no distinction between the 4th neural spine and the bony ridge of the skull. 8) Absence of an arch on the ventral side of the abdominal vertebra centrum (plesiomorphic in 
<taxonomicName id="2BF6117C856EDCADBA7FCD69892C8D6B" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F34DE64E-5530-4CC0-A5C5-3BD58430405D" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Glyptosternon" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Glyptosternon McClelland 1842:584" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Glyptosternon</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="5ED0AF52EAA955FA5F3124B0C10E5A02" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:25654FA9-3B1D-4464-8012-AEE3D499BCEB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Glaridoglanis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Glaridoglanis Norman 1925:574" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Glaridoglanis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="0A40B03E8FDE3FE711BD26031C6C9A2A" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:987310A1-9E85-4272-AD9D-9DB5D24D6779" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Exostoma" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Exostoma Blyth 1860:155" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Exostoma</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="091CB3216A8B9C923C54019BB8FCFE89" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pareuchiloglanis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sinensis">Pareuchiloglanis sinensis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7D77DC7C2451041CFA09151AED548799" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:1FF87FDA-252E-4ABC-95C3-566EAC89B6D7" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pareuchiloglanis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pareuchiloglanis anteanalis Fang, Xu &amp; Cui 1984:209 (English p. 211)" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anteanalis">P. anteanalis</taxonomicName>
). 9) Post-haemapophysis of the 5th vertebra developed. 10) 5th parapophysis undeveloped and far shorter than the 4th parapophysis. 11) Pectoral spine soft and enveloped in the skin of the fin. 12) 2nd proximal of dorsal fin without wide lateral process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
