<subSubSection id="C6E5674705ADF40F3ED5AB08BEC88984" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2433E854F01683ED2C672B7B7FBAD1C9" lastPageNumber="63" pageNumber="62">
Following the review of published data and the examination of specimens, we recognize nine genera of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A5A44978397FF5E712B55FEAD32D84" pageNumber="62" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Glyptosternina">Glyptosternina</taxonomicName>
. Traits used to diagnose these genera include the development of the post-labial grove on the lower jaw (Fig. 17), the degree to which the gill openings extend onto the venter, dentition of the upper and lower jaws, and the number of branched pectoral rays (Tables 5-7). In Table 5, genera are separated into three phenetic 
<pageStartToken id="EDFC0BE81CDB4870D39718BE89948D78" pageNumber="63">groups</pageStartToken>
based on the development of the post-labial groove. In Table 6, characters are given to differentiate genera with an interrupted post-labial groove on the lower jaw, and in Table 7, characters are used to differentiate genera with a continuous post-labial groove on the lower jaw. Although these traits may result in the over-splitting of 
<taxonomicName id="A4C67885304A7DBEA7EE54621CBF7CF6" pageNumber="62" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Glyptosternina">Glyptosternina</taxonomicName>
genera, they do successfully diagnose the genera currently recognized by most authors. However, it should be noted that He (1996b) concluded that 
<taxonomicName id="3EE4894116181335C5596FE9E6D35DBB" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:1C6AC061-0134-487B-9102-EFF719A47063" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pareuchiloglanis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pareuchiloglanis Pellegrin 1936:245" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pareuchiloglanis</taxonomicName>
, as currently defined, is monophyletic only when species currently assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="4473743ABE8F123E8660465FC4A29893" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:AC273B3A-FA06-469F-9A73-E1E5BD9033D6" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudexostoma" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Pseudexostoma Chu 1979:78, 81" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Pseudexostoma</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CF1A54CC10BAA6BD41B06A5AE5187BBF" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:E68EC2A2-F2FB-48AE-BBCE-ABCFD9555304" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Oreoglanis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Oreoglanis Smith 1933:70" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="62" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Oreoglanis</taxonomicName>
are included.
</paragraph>
